
<p>
  To change the theme of a blog, first extract the content of the theme archive to the directory with the BlazeBlogger repository:
</p>

<pre>tar xfz <em>theme_name</em>.tar.gz</pre>

<p>
  Then move the template file and the corresponding style sheet to <code>.blaze/theme/</code> and <code>.blaze/style/</code> respectively:
</p>

<pre>mv <em>theme_name</em>.html .blaze/theme/
mv <em>theme_name</em>.css .blaze/style/</pre>

<p>
  Finally, change the configuration to use this theme:
</p>

<pre>blaze-config blog.theme <em>theme_name</em>.html
blaze-config blog.style <em>theme_name</em>.css</pre>

<p>
  The changes take effect the next time you run the <code>blaze-make</code> command.
</p>

